                            <comment id="13180166" author="zhihyu@ebaysf.com" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 03:47:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since ColumnInterpreters aren&apos;t limited to specific tables, approach from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4554&quot; title=&quot;Allow set/unset coprocessor table attributes from shell.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4554&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4554&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; cannot be used here.&lt;br/&gt;
I thought of adding load method in RegionCoprocessorHost for ColumnInterpreters. But RegionCoprocessorHost only loads system and table coprocessors in its ctor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;May need advice from coprocessor gurus about the proper solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13180517" author="zhihyu@ebaysf.com" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 16:52:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An alternative is to associate custom jar files (containing, e.g., ColumnInterpreter implementations) with tables.&lt;br/&gt;
Such association is expressed by a known table attribute.&lt;br/&gt;
There is redundancy in this approach, but we don&apos;t need to create new container.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
